@Node "Introduction" "reportguide.guide/Introduction"
@Next "Variables"
@Prev "Copyright"
@Toc "Main"

Introduction
************

Some UMS tools make extensive and significant manipulations to the
message base. Often the manipulations' calculations and responses of
UMS are printed out to standard output device (StdOut), i.e. the
Shell/CLI; for example see the output of SetExpire. If these tools are
executed automatically (by a shell script), it is desireable to save
these output. So why not save this stuff in an UMS message delivered to
the user it concerns? It is like the behaviour of cron under UNIX: the
cron daemon sends mail with the executed program's output to the owner
of the crontab entry.

   But report messages shall not be a substitute for error message
output to StdOut: report messages are optional.

   Several ways of sending these messages exist: Some 'sysop' want it
as mail (= private message) to a certain account, while other like them
in a newsgroup (= public message). To prevent extra variable entries in
@{b}ums.config@{ub} for every program and option, this guideline was created. It
shall standardize the manner of generating report messages (short:
reports).


@EndNode

@Node "Variables" "reportguide.guide/Variables"
@Next "Header"
@Prev "Introduction"
